24
24 is a 2016 Indian Tamil-language science fiction action film.<SEP>24 is the title of the film, centered around the theme of time control.<SEP>24 is the title of the film, which deals with time travel.

Vikram Kumar
Vikram Kumar is a director who changed the screenplay of the film with new dimensions in narration.<SEP>Vikram Kumar is the director of the film.<SEP>Vikram Kumar is the writer and director of the film 24.

Suriya
Suriya is an actor who played triple roles in the film 24 and whose production company announced the project.<SEP>Suriya is an actor who plays a triple role in the film as Manikandan 'Mani', Athreya, and Dr. Sethuraman.<SEP>Suriya is the producer of the film 24 and also stars in triple roles.

Samantha Ruth Prabhu
Samantha Ruth Prabhu is an actress who stars in the film 24.<SEP>Samantha Ruth Prabhu plays Sathyabhama aka Sathya, Mani's love interest.<SEP>Samantha Ruth Prabhu was finalized to play a leading female role in the film.

Nithya Menen
Nithya Menen is an actress who stars in the film 24.<SEP>Nithya Menen plays Priya Sethuraman, Sethuraman's wife and Mani's biological mother.<SEP>Nithya Menen was roped in to play another leading character in the film.

Tirru
Tirru is the cinematographer for the film 24.

Prawin Pudi
Prawin Pudi is the editor for the film 24.

A. R. Rahman
A. R. Rahman composed the songs and score for the film 24.<SEP>A. R. Rahman is the composer of the film's soundtrack and score.<SEP>A. R. Rahman was announced as the film soundtrack and score composer.

Qutub-E-Kripa
Qutub-E-Kripa contributed to the score of the film 24.

2D Entertainment
2D Entertainment is Suriya's production company that announced the film project.<SEP>2D Entertainment is Suriya's production company, which announced the project in August 2014.<SEP>2D Entertainment is the production company for the film 24, owned by Suriya.

Eros International
Eros International is a distributor of the film 24.

Studio Green
Studio Green is a distributor of the film 24.

India
India is the country of origin for the film 24.

Tamil
Tamil is the language of the film 24.

Mumbai
Mumbai is a city in India where principal photography for the film commenced.<SEP>Mumbai is a location where principal photography for the film 24 commenced.

Nasik
Nasik is a location where principal photography for the film 24 continued.

Goregaon
Goregaon is a location where principal photography for the film 24 continued.<SEP>Goregaon is a suburb of Mumbai where Filmistaan Studios is located.

Pune
Pune is a city in India where Subrata Roy Sahara Stadium is located.<SEP>Pune is a location where principal photography for the film 24 continued.

Poland
Poland is a country where a twenty-day schedule was filmed, including action scenes and songs.<SEP>Poland is a location where the second phase of filming for the film 24 was done.

Chennai
Chennai is a city in India where Adithyaram Studios is located.<SEP>Chennai is a city where filming commenced at AVM Studios.<SEP>Chennai is a location where filming for the film 24 was completed.

Vairamuthu
Vairamuthu is a lyricist who wrote lyrics for the songs in the film.<SEP>Vairamuthu wrote the lyrics for the film 24.

Madhan Karky
Madhan Karky is a lyricist who wrote lyrics for the songs in the film.<SEP>Madhan Karky wrote the lyrics for the film 24.

Sethuraman
Sethuraman is a character in the film, with Nithya Menen playing his love interest.<SEP>Sethuraman is a scientist and watchmaker who invents a time-traveling watch in the film 24.<SEP>Sethuraman is a scientist, Athreya's twin brother, and Mani's biological father. He initially creates the time-traveling watch and ultimately uses it to kill Athreya and protect his family.

Priya
Priya is Sethuraman's wife and Mani's biological mother. She is initially excited about the time travel but becomes wary of its dangers and asks Sethuraman to throw the watch away.<SEP>Priya is Sethuraman's wife and Manikandan's mother, who is killed by Athreya.

Manikandan
Manikandan, also called Mani, is Sethuraman and Priya's son, who grows up to be a watch mechanic.

Athreya
Athreya is Sethuraman's twin brother and a gangster who seeks to obtain the time-traveling watch.<SEP>Athreya is the antagonist character in the film, portrayed as wicked and smart.<SEP>Athreya is the main antagonist and Sethuraman's twin brother. He is initially portrayed as vicious and murderous, seeking to control time travel for his own purposes. He is later killed by Sethuraman.

Sathyabhama
Sathyabhama is the woman who takes care of Manikandan after Sethuraman entrusts him to her.

Sathya
Sathya is a girl who Mani meets and falls in love with.<SEP>Sathya is a young girl who interacts with Mani at the end of the film.

Mithran
Mithran is Athreya's trusted confidante.

Saravanan
Saravanan is Mani's friend.

24 (2016 Film)
A 2016 Indian Tamil-language science fiction action film directed by Vikram Kumar.

Samantha
An actress starring in the film 24.

₹70 crore
The budget of the film 24.

₹100 crore
The estimated box office collection of the film 24.

Time-Traveling Watch
An invention of Sethuraman that allows time travel, and is the central object of conflict in the film.

6 May 2016
The release date of the film 24.

64th National Film Awards
The event where 24 won two awards.

Critics Best Actor Award
The award Suriya won at the 64th Filmfare Awards.

64th Filmfare Awards
The event where Suriya won the Critics Best Actor Award.

Best Cinematography
One of the awards won by the film 24 at the 64th National Film Awards.

Best Production Design
One of the awards won by the film 24 at the 64th National Film Awards.

1990
1990 is the year Mani travels back to in an attempt to warn his parents about Athreya.<SEP>The year in which Sethuraman completes his time-traveling watch and is attacked by Athreya.

2016
The year in which Manikandan discovers the time-traveling watch and Athreya wakes up from his coma.

₹5 crore
The reward offered for the lost watch.

Mani
Mani is a character in the film, with Samantha playing his love interest.<SEP>Mani is a watch mechanic and Sethuraman's biological son. He is the only one who can upgrade the time-traveling watch. He travels back in time to warn his parents about Athreya's plans.

Sathyabhama aka Sathya
Sathyabhama, also known as Sathya, is Mani's love interest. She meets Sethuraman and Priya on a train and invites them to join her family's school.

AVM Studios
AVM Studios is a film studio in Chennai where sets were replicated for filming.

The Times of India
The Times of India is a newspaper that interviewed Vikram Kumar about the film.<SEP>The Times of India is a newspaper where Vikram gave an interview about his film.

World Athletics Championship
The World Athletics Championship is a global sports competition featuring top athletes in track and field.

Tamil Cinema
Tamil Cinema is the industry in which Ileana D'Cruz was to be relaunched.

Saranya Ponvannan
Saranya Ponvannan plays Sathyabhama, Mani's adoptive mother.<SEP>Saranya Ponvannan plays the role of Mani's mother in the film.

Ajay
Ajay plays Mithran, Athreya's trusted sidekick.

Girish Karnad
Girish Karnad plays Sathyabhama and Raghu's father, Sathya's grandfather.

Mohan Raman
Mohan Raman plays Raghu, Sathya's father.

Sudha
Sudha plays Sathya's mother.

Sathyan
Sathyan plays Saravanan, Mani's friend.

Charle
Charle plays Reddiyar.

Appukutty
Appukutty plays Reddiyar's staff.

Harsha Vardhan
Harsha Vardhan plays Kalai, an electrician who works for Athreya.

Natarajan Balkrishna
Natarajan Balkrishna plays Sathya's uncle.

T. S. Ranganathan
T. S. Ranganathan plays Sathya's uncle.

Mohan Natarajan
Mohan Natarajan is the producer who initially backed the film.

Vikram
Vikram is a film director who discussed a gadget playing an important role in a movie.<SEP>Vikram is an actor who was initially considered for the lead role.

Harris Jayaraj
Harris Jayaraj was confirmed to score the music for the film.

P. C. Sreeram
P. C. Sreeram was to handle the film cinematography.

Ileana D'Cruz
Ileana D'Cruz was signed to do the film and was to be her re-launch in Tamil cinema.

Mahesh Babu
Mahesh Babu was considered for the lead role but passed on the offer.

Office
The office is the location where Athreya confronts Mani and brutally attacks him.

Watch
The watch is a time-traveling device central to the plot, capable of transporting its wearer through time, though initially limited to 24-hour jumps.

School
The school is the location where Sethuraman and Priya are invited to work as a science teacher and his wife, respectively.

Original Back
The original back is a distinguishing feature of Mani's copy of the watch, indicating its authenticity.

Hand
The hand is the body part that Athreya chops off of Mani in a brutal attack.

Incurable Disease
An incurable disease is the false ailment Athreya pretends to have while disguised as Sethuraman to trick Mani.

Parents' Death
The death of Mani's parents is the event that Mani seeks to prevent by traveling back in time.

Henchmen
Henchmen are the people who work for Athreya and assist him in his evil deeds.

Train
The train is the location where Sethuraman and Priya meet Sathyabhama.

Science Teacher
A science teacher is the profession Sethuraman claims to have when meeting Sathyabhama on the train.

Watch Mechanic
A watch mechanic is Mani's profession.

Scientist
A scientist is Sethuraman's profession.

Twin Brother
Twin brother is the relationship between Athreya and Sethuraman.

Love Interest
Love interest is the relationship between Mani and Sathyabhama.

Wife
Wife is the relationship between Priya and Sethuraman.

Adoptive Mother
Adoptive mother is the relationship between Saranya Ponvannan and Mani.

Sidekick
Sidekick is the relationship between Ajay and Athreya.

Father
Father is the relationship between Girish Karnad and Sathyabhama.

Mother
Mother is the relationship between Sudha and Sathyabhama.

Friend
Friend is the relationship between Sathyan and Mani.

Staff
Staff is the relationship between Appukutty and Reddiyar.

Electrician
Electrician is the profession of Harsha Vardhan.

Uncle
Uncle is the relationship between Natarajan Balkrishna and Sathyabhama.

Director
Director is the profession of Vikram Kumar.

Producer
Producer is the profession of Mohan Natarajan.

Actor
Actor is the profession of Vikram.

Music
Music is the profession of Harris Jayaraj.

Cinematography
Cinematography is the profession of P. C. Sreeram.

Triple Role
Triple role is the role of Suriya in the film.

Twitter
Twitter is a social media platform used by 2D Entertainment to announce the film project.

Catherine Tresa
Catherine Tresa was considered for the lead female role in the film.

Nashik
Nashik is a city in India where a romantic song was filmed for the movie.

Filmistaan Studios
Filmistaan Studios in Goregaon is where certain scenes and VFX works were carried out.

Kraków
Kraków is a city in Poland where filming took place.

Kraków Film Commission
The Kraków Film Commission supported the film project in Poland.

Kraków Film Cluster
The Kraków Film Cluster supported the film project in Poland.

Subrata Roy Sahara Stadium
Subrata Roy Sahara Stadium in Pune is where an important sequence was shot.

Adithyaram Studios
Adithyaram Studios in Chennai is where the last schedule of filming was done.

Eros Music
Eros Music released the soundtrack album of the film.

Sony Music India
Sony Music India later bought the rights to the soundtrack album.

Gadget
A gadget plays an important role in the movie, appealing to a wide audience.

August 2014
August 2014 is when 2D Entertainment announced the project.

October 2014
October 2014 is when A. R. Rahman was announced as the film's composer.

February 2015
February 2015 is when Samantha Ruth Prabhu was finalized for the lead female role.

July 2015
July 2015 is when Nithya Menen was roped in to play another leading character.

8 April 2015
8 April 2015 is when principal photography commenced in Mumbai.

Early June 2015
Early June 2015 is when a romantic song was filmed in Nashik.

September 2015
September 2015 is when VFX works were carried out at Filmistaan studios.

1 August 2015
1 August 2015 is when Nithya Menen began filming her portions in the city.

Early September 2015
Early September 2015 is when the first schedule was completed.

Mid September 2015
Mid September 2015 is when a twenty-day schedule began in Poland.

30 September 2015
30 September 2015 is when the second schedule of filming in Poland was wrapped up.

26 October 2015
26 October 2015 is when the team shot an important sequence in Subrata Roy Sahara Stadium in Pune.

End of October 2015
End of October 2015 is when the last schedule of filming was done at Adithyaram Studios in Chennai.

2 November 2015
2 November 2015 is when the filming was completed.

100 Days of Filming
The film was shot for over 100 days, indicating a significant production timeline.

VFX
More than 60 percent of the film involves VFX, highlighting its importance in the film's production.

9 April 2016
9 April 2016 is when the soundtrack album was released by Eros Music.

Athreya's Looks
Five to six looks were designed for the antagonist character Athreya, indicating the character's complexity.

Cinelight
Cinelight is a Kraków Company that provided the lights for filming in Poland.
